Commentary Text: Woakes to Sam Curran, out Bowled!! Knocked him over! That's stopped on him from a length, not particularly full, Sam Curran tries swatting it cross-batted into the on-side stands, but is beaten by the surprising tackiness of the wicket and that's crashed into the stumps. No matter, that's a terrific innings from Sam Curran to finish things off for CSK, who end up with a competitive 188/7. Sam Curran b Woakes 34(15) [4s-4 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Avesh Khan to Dhoni, out Bowled! Stop the press - Dhoni departs for a duck! That's skidding through in line with the stumps, not exactly true bounce, and Dhoni throws his weight behind the pull only for the ball to kiss his under-edge and crash into the stumps, lighting up the bails in a flash - the one display of lights that can silence an imaginary crowd at an Indian venue. Dhoni departs for a duck in his first appearance in IPL 2021. No finisher heroics tonight, then. Dhoni b Avesh Khan 0(2)

Commentary Text: Avesh Khan to Jadeja, out Raina Run Out!! 1 run completed. Raina has been sold down the river! Jadeja tucks this one off the thigh off a hop towards deep backward square leg, and runs through for a quick single, but as he turns back, the bowler is in his way and he decides to abort the second - too late though, as Raina has already made his way back for the second. The throw comes into the striker's end, and Pant has whipped off the bails. Raina, unfortunately, has been sold down the river. Not necessarily by Jadeja, but by unfortunate circumstance without any obvious villains. In fact, Jadeja tries to tell Raina that the bowler came in the way, but Raina just puts his head down and walks back. Raina run out (Woakes/Pant) 54(36) [4s-3 6s-4]

Commentary Text: Ashwin to Moeen Ali, out Caught by Dhawan!! Oh dear! What have to you done, Moeen? Two lovely sixes and he tries something that doesn't come naturally for him. Looked classy with the lofted drives, but now attempts a cheeky little reverse sweep. Got into a terrible position, the extra bounce didn't help either - looked very awkward as he executed the shot. A big top-edge on the shot, but it still needed to be caught. Dhawan circled around it as he ran back from short third man, kept his eyes on the ball and completed a two-handed catch, over his right shoulder. Not an easy catch, but this is a timely wicket for the Capitals. Moeen was just beginning to put the pressure back on them. The players will take a strategic time-out as well. Moeen Ali c Dhawan b Ashwin 36(24) [4s-4 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Avesh Khan to du Plessis, out Lbw!! du Plessis has been given OUT LBW. He doesn't look too convinced, his partner came rushing across, but he's not waiting, no review - off he goes. That looks plumb on second viewing, a duck for du Plessis and Avesh has struck in his first over - the nip-backer and it once again does the trick, du Plessis is caught on the front-foot as he drove, past the inside edge and struck him right in front of off - was going on and crashing into the middle-stump.
